  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: COMPOUND-03)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed combinations, and the assessment team concluded that the overall evidence base is sufficiently mature to warrant a Medium assurance level. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated; the majority achieved levels commensurate with or approaching required levels, and the validation dataset spans physiologically representative operating conditions. The decision record reflects the team's integrated judgment that residual gaps are bounded and manageable within the device's design-control framework.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-absolute",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-experimental-mrl5"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
